    <!-- Help Activity -->
    <string name="help_title">Help and more</string>
    <string name="help_intro">This app allows you to block internet access for your apps using two methods: Shizuku (recommended) or a local VPN (fallback) without root requirement.</string>
    <string name="help_shizuku_title">1. Shizuku Mode</string>
    <string name="help_shizuku_desc">This mode uses Shizuku to apply firewall rules directly to the system. It is efficient and does not require a constant background service. And doesn\'t need the app to be constantly running. \n\nTo use it, you must first download and activate Shizuku:</string>
    <string name="help_shizuku_link">https://github.com/RikkaApps/Shizuku</string>
    <string name="help_vpn_title">2. VPN Mode</string>
    <string name="help_vpn_desc">This mode runs a local VPN service on your phone. All app traffic passes through this service, which blocks connections for the apps you select. This mode must be running constantly to work.</string>
    <string name="help_usage_title">3. How to Use</string>
    <string name="help_usage_desc">The firewall is DISABLED by default.\n\n1. Press the \"Enable\" button on the main screen to start the firewall.\n\n2. Toggle the switch to select your mode (Shizuku or VPN).\n\n3. Tap the Wi-Fi or Data icons next to an app to block or allow its internet access for that mode. for Shizuku both are linked for now.\n\nAfter a reboot, you must open this app (and Shizuku, if used) and press \"Enable\" again to re-apply your settings. hit refresh button in the app, enable/disable or clear cache and force stop and reboot to troubleshoot.\n\n Made by shynoid/shayan. </string>
